<section class="w-full flex justify-center">
    <div class="w-full max-w-3xl px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 md:py-24 reveal">
        <div class="text-center mb-10">
            <p
                class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gold mb-4"
            >
                The origin story
            </p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">
                First-time dog people
            </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-muted">
            <p>
                The Davis family had never had a dog before Nala. We were
                complete novices — unsure of what we were getting into, but
                excited for the adventure ahead.
            </p>
            <p>
                When she first arrived, she was a tiny bundle of golden fluff
                with paws too big for her body and eyes full of curiosity. She
                sniffed every corner of the house and immediately claimed the
                comfiest spots as her own.
            </p>
            <p>
                Learning to care for her was a journey. We read books, watched
                videos, and made plenty of mistakes along the way. But through
                every chewed shoe, every 3&nbsp;a.m. potty break, and every
                muddy paw print on the floor, our love for her only grew
                stronger.
            </p>
            <p>
                She taught us patience, responsibility, and the pure joy of
                unconditional love — the tail wag when we come home, the spin at
                the word "walk," the gentle nuzzle when we're feeling down. Those
                are the moments that make it all worth it.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
